==English==
===Noun===
'''the nut behind the bolt'''
# The person using a firearm. Shooter.
#: He said the accident was caused by a faulty trigger, but I think it was the '''nut behind the bolt'''.
===Etymology===
Uses the word ''nut'' to refer to a fool, rather than a mechanical [[nut]].  Implies that most firearm accidents are the responsibility of the shooter and not a failure of the gun.